pragma solidity 0.8.9;

import "hardhat/console.sol";
import "./AgreementViolation.sol";

contract DataSharingAgreement {

    AgreementViolation public agreementViolation = new AgreementViolation();

    enum State { Created, Active, Updated, Violated, Terminated }

    struct Agreement {
        uint256 agreementId;
        string providerPublicKey;
        string consumerPublicKey;
        string dataExchangeAgreementHash;
        DataOffering dataOffering;
        string purpose;
        State state;
        string providerId;
        string consumerId;
        uint256[3] agreementDates;
        IntendedUse intendedUse;
        LicenseGrant licenseGrant;
        bool dataStream;
        bool signed;
    }

    struct DataOffering {
        string dataOfferingId; 
        uint256 dataOfferingVersion;
    }
    
    struct IntendedUse {
        bool processData;
        bool shareDataWithThirdParty;
        bool editData;
    }
    
    struct LicenseGrant {
        bool copyData;
        bool transferable;
        bool exclusiveness;
        bool revocable;
    }

    Agreement[] public agreements;

    uint256 activeAgreementCount;
    mapping (string => uint) providerCount;
    mapping (string => uint) providerActiveCount;
    mapping (string => uint) consumerCount;
    mapping (string => uint) consumerActiveCount;
    mapping (string => uint) consumerPublicKeyCount;
    mapping (string => uint) dataOfferingCount;

    event AgreementCreated(string providerId, string consumerId, uint256 id);
    event AgreementUpdated(string providerId, string consumerId, uint256 id);
    event AgreementSigned(string providerId, string consumerId, uint256 id);
    event SignedResolutionEvaluated(string providerId, string consumerId, uint256 id);
    event AgreementTerminated(string providerId, string consumerId,uint256 id);

    function createAgreement(
                            string memory _providerPublicKey,
                            string memory _consumerPublicKey,
                            string memory _dataExchangeAgreementHash,
                            DataOffering memory dataOffering,
                            string memory _purpose,
                            string memory _providerId,
                            string memory _consumerId,
                            uint256[] memory dates,
                            IntendedUse memory intendedUse,
                            LicenseGrant memory licenseGrant,
                            bool _dataStream
                            ) public {
                            
        Agreement memory newAgreement;
        newAgreement.providerPublicKey = _providerPublicKey;
        newAgreement.consumerPublicKey = _consumerPublicKey;
        newAgreement.dataExchangeAgreementHash = _dataExchangeAgreementHash;
        newAgreement.dataOffering.dataOfferingId = dataOffering.dataOfferingId;
        newAgreement.dataOffering.dataOfferingVersion = dataOffering.dataOfferingVersion;
        newAgreement.purpose = _purpose;
        newAgreement.providerId = _providerId;
        newAgreement.consumerId = _consumerId;
    
        newAgreement.state = State.Created;
        newAgreement.agreementDates[0] = dates[0]; 
        newAgreement.agreementDates[1] = dates[1];
     
        require ( dates[1] >= newAgreement.agreementDates[0], "Start date must be after creation date." );
        require ( dates[2] > dates[1], "End date must be after start date." );
        newAgreement.agreementDates[2] = dates[2];
        
        newAgreement.intendedUse.processData = intendedUse.processData;
        newAgreement.intendedUse.shareDataWithThirdParty = intendedUse.shareDataWithThirdParty;
        newAgreement.intendedUse.editData = intendedUse.editData;
        
        newAgreement.licenseGrant.copyData = licenseGrant.copyData;
        newAgreement.licenseGrant.transferable = licenseGrant.transferable;
        newAgreement.licenseGrant.exclusiveness = licenseGrant.exclusiveness;
        newAgreement.licenseGrant.revocable = licenseGrant.revocable;
        
        newAgreement.dataStream = _dataStream;
        

        newAgreement.agreementId = agreements.length;
        
        agreements.push(newAgreement);

        providerCount[_providerId]++;
        consumerCount[_consumerId]++;
        
        dataOfferingCount[dataOffering.dataOfferingId]++;
        
        emit AgreementCreated(_providerId, _consumerId, agreements.length - 1);  
    }
    
    function updateAgreement(uint256 _id,
                            string memory _providerPublicKey,
                            string memory _consumerPublicKey,
                            string memory _dataOfferingId,
                            string memory _purpose,
                            string memory _providerId,
                            string memory _consumerId,
                            uint256[] memory dates,
                            IntendedUse memory intendedUse,
                            LicenseGrant memory licenseGrant,
                            bool _dataStream) public {
       
        Agreement storage agreement = agreements[_id];  

        require (keccak256(abi.encodePacked(agreements[_id].providerId)) == keccak256(abi.encodePacked(_providerId)), "Not the provider of the agreement" ); 
        
        if(agreement.state == State.Active)
        {
            agreement.purpose = _purpose;
            agreement.agreementDates[1] = dates[0];
     
            require ( dates[0] >= agreement.agreementDates[0], "Start date must be after creation date." );
            require ( dates[1] > dates[0], "End date must be after start date." );
            agreement.agreementDates[2] = dates[1];
        
            agreement.intendedUse.processData = intendedUse.processData;
            agreement.intendedUse.shareDataWithThirdParty = intendedUse.shareDataWithThirdParty;
            agreement.intendedUse.editData = intendedUse.editData;
        
            agreement.licenseGrant.copyData = licenseGrant.copyData;
            agreement.licenseGrant.transferable = licenseGrant.transferable;
            agreement.licenseGrant.exclusiveness = licenseGrant.exclusiveness;
            agreement.licenseGrant.revocable = licenseGrant.revocable;

            agreement.dataStream = _dataStream;

            agreement.state = State.Updated;
            agreements[_id].signed = false;
            activeAgreementCount--;
            providerActiveCount[_providerId]--;
            consumerActiveCount[_consumerId]--;
            consumerPublicKeyCount[_consumerPublicKey]--;

            emit AgreementUpdated(_providerId, _consumerId, _id);
        }
    }

    function signAgreement (uint256 _id, string memory _consumerId) public {
        require (keccak256(abi.encodePacked(agreements[_id].consumerId)) == keccak256(abi.encodePacked(_consumerId)), "Not the consumer of agreement." );
    
        agreements[_id].signed = true;

        if(agreements[_id].agreementDates[2]>=block.timestamp) {
            agreements[_id].state = State.Active;
            activeAgreementCount++;
            providerActiveCount[agreements[_id].providerId]++;
            consumerActiveCount[_consumerId]++;
            consumerPublicKeyCount[agreements[_id].consumerPublicKey]++;
            emit AgreementSigned(agreements[_id].providerId,_consumerId, _id);
        }
    }

    function getAgreement(uint256 id) public view returns (Agreement memory) {
        return agreements[id];
    }

    function getAgreementsLength() public view returns (uint256) {
        return agreements.length;
    } 

     function getState(uint256 id) public view returns (State) {
        return agreements[id].state;
    } 
    
    function checkActiveAgreements () external view returns (Agreement[] memory) {
        Agreement[] memory activeAgreements = new Agreement[](activeAgreementCount);
        uint counter = 0;
        for (uint i = 0; i < agreements.length; i++){
            if(agreements[i].state == State.Active) {   
                activeAgreements[counter++] = agreements[i];
            }
        }
        return activeAgreements;
    }

    function checkAgreementsByConsumer (string memory _consumerId, bool active) external view returns (Agreement[] memory) {
        uint256 counter = 0;
        Agreement[] memory consumerAgreements;
        if(active) {
            consumerAgreements = new Agreement[](consumerActiveCount[_consumerId]);
            for (uint i = 0; i < agreements.length; i++)
                if (agreements[i].state == State.Active && keccak256(abi.encodePacked(agreements[i].consumerId)) == keccak256(abi.encodePacked(_consumerId))){
                    consumerAgreements[counter++] = agreements[i];
                }  
        }
        else {
            consumerAgreements = new Agreement[](consumerCount[_consumerId]);
            for (uint i = 0; i < agreements.length; i++)
                if (keccak256(abi.encodePacked(agreements[i].consumerId)) == keccak256(abi.encodePacked(_consumerId))){
                    consumerAgreements[counter++] = agreements[i];
                }
        }
        return consumerAgreements;
    }

    function checkAgreementsByProvider (string memory _providerId, bool active) external view returns (Agreement[] memory) {
        uint256 counter = 0;
        Agreement[] memory providerAgreements;
        if(active) {
            providerAgreements = new Agreement[](providerActiveCount[_providerId]);
            for (uint i = 0; i < agreements.length; i++)
                if (agreements[i].state == State.Active && keccak256(abi.encodePacked(agreements[i].providerId)) == keccak256(abi.encodePacked(_providerId))){
                    providerAgreements[counter++] = agreements[i];
                }  
        }
        else {
            providerAgreements = new Agreement[](providerCount[_providerId]);
            for (uint i = 0; i < agreements.length; i++)
                if (keccak256(abi.encodePacked(agreements[i].providerId)) == keccak256(abi.encodePacked(_providerId))){
                    providerAgreements[counter++] = agreements[i];
                }
        }
        return providerAgreements;
    }

    function checkAgreementsByDataOffering (string memory _dataOffering) external view returns (Agreement[] memory) {
        Agreement[] memory dataOfferingAgreements = new Agreement[](dataOfferingCount[_dataOffering]);
        uint counter = 0;
        for (uint i = 0; i < agreements.length; i++){
            if (keccak256(abi.encodePacked(agreements[i].dataOffering.dataOfferingId)) == keccak256(abi.encodePacked(_dataOffering))) {
                dataOfferingAgreements[counter++] = agreements[i];
            }
        }
        return dataOfferingAgreements;
    }
     
    function retrieveAgreements (string memory _consumerPublicKey) external view returns (Agreement[] memory, uint256 counter) {

        Agreement[] memory consumerPublicKeyAgreements = new Agreement[](consumerPublicKeyCount[_consumerPublicKey]);
        uint256 counter = 0;
        for (uint i = 0; i < agreements.length; i++){
            if (agreements[i].state == State.Active && agreements[i].agreementDates[1]<=block.timestamp && keccak256(abi.encodePacked(agreements[i].consumerPublicKey)) == keccak256(abi.encodePacked(_consumerPublicKey))) {
                consumerPublicKeyAgreements[counter++] = agreements[i];
            }
        }
        return (consumerPublicKeyAgreements, counter);
      
    }

    function evaluateSignedResolution(uint256 _agreementId, string memory _proofType, string memory _type, string memory _resolution,
                                string memory _dataExchangeId, uint256 _iat, string memory _iss, string memory _sub) public {

      agreementViolation.evaluateResolution(_agreementId, _proofType, _type, _resolution, _dataExchangeId, _iat, _iss, _sub);
      if(agreementViolation.getPenaltyChoices(_agreementId).length>0){
        agreements[_agreementId].state=State.Violated;
      }
      emit SignedResolutionEvaluated(agreements[_agreementId].providerId, agreements[_agreementId].consumerId, _agreementId);

	}

    function presentPenaltyChoices(uint256 _agreementId) public view returns (string[] memory) { 
        return agreementViolation.getPenaltyChoices(_agreementId);
    }


    function terminateAgreement(uint256 _id) public {
        if(agreements[_id].agreementDates[2]<=block.timestamp){
            if(agreements[_id].state == State.Active){
                activeAgreementCount--;
                providerActiveCount[agreements[_id].providerId]--;
                consumerActiveCount[agreements[_id].consumerId]--;
                consumerPublicKeyCount[agreements[_id].consumerPublicKey]--;
            }     
            agreements[_id].state = State.Terminated;
            emit AgreementTerminated(agreements[_id].providerId,agreements[_id].consumerId, _id);
        }
    }

    
}

import "hardhat/console.sol";
contract AgreementViolation {
    
    enum ViolationType {
        NotViolated,
        PaymentNotCompleted,
        DataNotTransferredAsDescribed,
        DataNotAsDescribed,
        LicenseViolated
    }

    enum ResolutionType { Verification, Dispute }
    enum ResolutionState { Completed, NotCompleted, Accepted, Denied }

    struct Violation {
        ViolationType violationType;
        string issuerId;
    }

    struct SignedResolution {
        string proofType;
        string resolutionType;
        string resolution;
        string dataExchangeId;
        uint256 iat;
        string iss;
        string sub;
    }
    
    
    mapping(uint256 => Violation) public violations;

    mapping(uint256 => string) public penalties;

    mapping(uint256 => string[]) public agreementIdToPenalties;

    
    function evaluateResolution(
        uint256 _agreementId,
        string memory _proofType,
        string memory _type,
        string memory _resolution,
        string memory _dataExchangeId,
        uint256 _iat,
        string memory _iss,
        string memory _sub) public { 

        SignedResolution memory signedResolution;
        signedResolution.proofType = _proofType;
        signedResolution.resolutionType = _type;
        signedResolution.resolution = _resolution;
        signedResolution.dataExchangeId = _dataExchangeId;
        signedResolution.iat = _iat;
        signedResolution.iss = _iss;   
        signedResolution.sub = _sub;

        if(keccak256(abi.encodePacked(signedResolution.resolution)) == keccak256(abi.encodePacked("completed"))){
                            delete agreementIdToPenalties[_agreementId];
             
        }
        else if(keccak256(abi.encodePacked(signedResolution.resolution)) == keccak256(abi.encodePacked("notCompleted"))) { 
                //Decryption key not published (data tranfer not as described)
                issueViolation(_agreementId,ViolationType.DataNotTransferredAsDescribed, signedResolution.sub);
                setPenalties(_agreementId);       
        }
        else if(keccak256(abi.encodePacked(signedResolution.resolution)) == keccak256(abi.encodePacked("accepted"))){ 
                issueViolation(_agreementId,ViolationType.DataNotTransferredAsDescribed, signedResolution.sub);
                setPenalties(_agreementId);
             }
        else if(keccak256(abi.encodePacked(signedResolution.resolution)) == keccak256(abi.encodePacked("denied")))
                //The cipherblock can be properly decrypted
                 delete agreementIdToPenalties[_agreementId];

    }

    function getPenaltyChoices(uint256 _agreementId) public view returns (string[] memory){
        return agreementIdToPenalties[_agreementId];
    }
    

    function issueViolation(uint256 _agreementId, ViolationType _violationType, string memory _issuerId) private {
        violations[_agreementId] = Violation(_violationType, _issuerId);
    }

    function setPenalties(uint256 _agreementId) private {
        agreementIdToPenalties[_agreementId].push("Terminate");
        agreementIdToPenalties[_agreementId].push("NewEndDate");
        agreementIdToPenalties[_agreementId].push("NewEndDateAndReductionOfPayment"); 
    }

    function getViolation(uint256 _agreementId) public view returns (Violation memory){
        return violations[_agreementId];
    }

    function getPenalty(uint256 _agreementId) public view returns (string memory){
        return penalties[_agreementId];
    }
